						<div class="postbody">While I back up what tokumaru said for the most part, I'd still say that, if the sprites are handled &quot;properly&quot;, this means metasprites are copied to individual sprites into shadow OAM every frame, a lot of sprites will tend to also greatly influence the CPU load, because decoding/moving all those metasprites into OAM with effects applied on them can take a lot of time.<br /><br />So it's wrong to say a game slowing down is because lots of objects and not because lots of sprites. I could be one, the other, or (the most likely) a combination of both.</div>

