					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The other thing is that if the game isn't structured in such a way that slowdown happens gracefully, very often it will be accompanied by rendering glitches, especially where a status bar or some kind of scroll split is involved. For example, TMNT's status bar will disappear on alternating frames during slowdown. Unless your game has no special rendering techniques, keeping it together despite slowdown usually requires careful planning and delegation of important timed tasks to the NMI (scroll splits, music, etc.).</div>

